Funky Friday Flow 💜

Use this fun, yoga transition as an advanced replacement for Chaturanga jump back or advancement to knee to nose tiger pose. 🐅

Basic Cues:
🧘‍♀️inhale Three Legged Dog swing your right leg towards the sky exhale knee across the body to a fallen triangle kick (beginner level say knee to opposite elbow).
🧘🏽‍♂️ Advanced option, walk your legs and hands closer together in downdog and land in side crow.
(Insider tip: keep your knees vent in both parts of the transition going up and going down to make it easier.)
🧘‍♀️Aim to land your right cheek on the mat and find the hover point.
🧘🏾 Jab your left elbow into your IT band for support and if your flexibility allows, your right elbow jabs your right outer butt/hip.
🧘🏽‍♀️ to transition out there’s two options: fallen triangle then three-legged dog
🧘‍♀️from side crow place your right leg down for fallen triangle and then re-extend into three-legged dog. Side crow =>Jump Back
🧘🏾 Jump back your supported side crow right leg into low chaturanga, and your left foot is now naturally hovering

Funky Friday Flow 💜

Part of why I love yoga is the creative play between poetry, music, and dance. Use this fun, yoga transition as an advanced replacement for Chaturanga push-ups.

Basic Cues
🧘‍♀️From a low lunge position, inhale Three Legged Dog swing your right leg towards the sky, with a micro bend in both of your knees
🧘‍♀️Advanced option, micro ban your elbows carefully into dolphin pose
((Insider tip: keep your knees vent in both parts of the transition going up and going down to make it easier ))
🧘‍♀️Aim to simultaneously drop both elbows at the same time with your fingers facing forward and your palms flat against the ground to tone your triceps even more
🧘‍♀️From three like a dolphin, look at your thumbs, maintain slight bend in left bottom leg, push FORWARD off of your elbows into plank
🧘‍♀️Option to do a push-up or single leg, push-up or advanced option flutter kick #chinstand leaning your chin forward kiss the mat lightly and use your elbows as kick stands to support your lower ribs
🧘‍♀️Lift through your top leg like there was a puppeteer pulling a string with your leg skyward. 
🧘‍♀️Bend your knees to make the flutter kick less intense on your low back. (Insider Tip - General rule of thumb, anytime you bend at your knees or elbows it makes it less intense on the medial axis a.k.a. your torso, low abs, chest and shoulders)

It’s time for #FridayFlow with Katie B! 🧘‍♀️ Let’s work that full bind. 

So, prayer twist is where you start and then go into half bind.

If you're somebody who's newer to binds, you can wear your strap around you like a belt and try it like I demonstrate here. 

Whatever bind you're in, hold steady if you want to try the full bind.

The trick is actually getting the dark side of your palm and shoving it through the pelvis. You can see I'm feeding my hands all the way through and then I grab it.

Then, step your back foot so your knee comes off the ground.

If you want a bound triangle, step your left foot forward and it’s a revolved bound pyramid triangle.

You know you’re doing the right post when it’s a little hard to breathe!

Try this pose this weekend and see how you do! 💜💪

👉Start at Downward Dog then exhale into three-legged dog and then take your knee to your nose and drop your knee down into modified side plank

👉Inhale and lift your left arm high, then move into twisted down dog

👉Right leg extends again and inhale into three-legged dog, then have your right leg step through into forward lunge

👉Move into modified crescent or full crescent and push bad energy out and hop

👉Drop your knee to big back bend and move hands to the nape of your neck

👉Twisted low lunge into side plank or fallen warrior and inhale

👉Exhale into Chaturanga and breathe into upward dog

Repeat on both sides and go through as many times as you desire. If you want to add or remove anything fun, please do.

moment by moment
human by human
breath by breath

heart to heart.

a genuine embrace,
your cold breath in on winter’s night
